title: Pappus' theorem
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$A,B,C$$ be points on one line in a [[projective plane|Projective space]] $$P(V)$$ and let $$A',B',C'$$ be points on another line. Then the points
$$
C''=AB'\cap A'B,\quad A''=BC'\cap B'C,\quad B''=CA'\cap C'A
$$
lie on a line.

This is a special case of [[Pascal's theorem]].